<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,878,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,878,904]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Description</emphasis>
:—All tepals white or sometimes inner tepals adaxially yellow (the rest of the description follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Liang, S. Y. &amp; Tamura, M." pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="24" refId="ref7281" refString="Liang, S. Y. &amp; Tamura, M. (2000) Lilium L .. In: Wu, Z. Y. &amp; Raven, P. H. (eds.) Flora of China 24. Science Press, Beijing; &amp; Missouri" type="book chapter" year="2000">Liang &amp; Tamura 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,878,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,498,950,976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Forests, grassy slopes; 
<quantity box="[797,956,950,977]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" unit="m" value="2800.0" valueMax="3600.0" valueMin="2000.0">2000–3600 m</quantity>
(based on annotated specimens). 
<collectingRegion box="[1354,1447,950,976]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,225,987,1013]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[236,363,986,1012]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[374,474,986,1012]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,878,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[189,426,1022,1048]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[189,426,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Lilium jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and typified from cultivated material at Kunming Botanical Garden (Peng 84-23!) derived from bulbs originally collected on Jinfo Mountain (
<collectingRegion box="[918,1200,1058,1084]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Chongqing and Guizhou</collectingRegion>
provinces). Based on the published material, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[400,584,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[400,584,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Franchet (1892: 319)" authorityName="Franchet" authorityPageNumber="319" authorityYear="1892" box="[734,1096,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis box="[734,851,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Franchet, A. R." box="[858,1096,1094,1120]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="305 - 321" refId="ref6994" refString="Franchet, A. R. (1892) Les Lis de la Chine et du Thibet. Journal de Botanique (Morot) 6: 305 - 321." type="journal article" year="1892">Franchet (1892: 319)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having more purple spots at the throat of flower and yellowish tepals. However, we have observed purple spots and yellowish flowers in natural populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[306,423,1166,1192]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis box="[306,423,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in northwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[777,863,1167,1193]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[879,1002,1166,1193]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,187,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[154,1434,187,1884]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Flowers of Lilium taliense Franchet from NW Yunnan showng continuous morphological variations in tepal spots andcolor i.e., white to yellow). Materials representing populations from A, Wengshui, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-56, PE) showing variability of spot tepal spots; B, Gezan, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-10, PE) showing variability of tepal color on a single individual; C, Jinfo Mountain, the type locality of L. jinfushanense exhibiting yellow inner tepals." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142425/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Thus, the spots and tepal color appear insufficient to justify the species status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[633,820,1202,1228]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[633,820,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We more rigorously compared 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[1199,1386,1202,1228]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">L. jinfushanense</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">L. taliense</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
by visiting the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[403,588,1238,1264]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[403,588,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[596,644,1239,1265]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
locality at Jinfo Mountain. There, we observed three populations of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with inner tepals having yellowish coloring on their adaxial surfaces (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1132,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,187,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[154,1434,187,1884]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Flowers of Lilium taliense Franchet from NW Yunnan showng continuous morphological variations in tepal spots andcolor i.e., white to yellow). Materials representing populations from A, Wengshui, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-56, PE) showing variability of spot tepal spots; B, Gezan, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-10, PE) showing variability of tepal color on a single individual; C, Jinfo Mountain, the type locality of L. jinfushanense exhibiting yellow inner tepals." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142425/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) and, thus, bearing striking resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[307,489,1310,1336]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[307,489,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also noticed that the cultivated 
<typeStatus box="[879,927,1311,1337]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[1071,1252,1310,1336]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[1071,1252,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits narrower leaves compared to the native populations. We speculate that the observed variation in leaf size may be indicative of unpredictable phenotypic expression under cultivation. The available morphological data appear insufficient for considering 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[278,467,1418,1444]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[278,467,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species. Moreover, molecular phylogenetic analyses have resolved the yellow-tepal taxon from the 
<typeStatus box="[459,507,1455,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
locality within 
<taxonomicName box="[686,804,1454,1480]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis box="[686,804,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Hohenegger, M. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J." box="[819,999,1454,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="69 - 85" refId="ref7024" refString="Gao, Y. D., Hohenegger, M., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D., He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J. (2012) A new species in the genus Nomocharis Franchet (Liliaceae): evidence that brings the genus Nomocharis into Lilium. Plant Systematics and Evolution 298: 69 - 85. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 011 - 0524 - 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[875,926,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J." box="[1011,1084,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="443 - 460" refId="ref7112" refString="Gao, Y. D., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. (2013 a) Evolutionary events in Lilium (including Nomocharis, Liliaceae) are temporally correlated with orogenies of the Q - T plateau and the HDM. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 68: 443 - 460. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2013.04.026" type="journal article" year="2013">2013a</bibRefCitation>
), and this supports our proposed treatment. A more broadly circumscribed 
<taxonomicName box="[617,737,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis box="[617,737,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[870,1056,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis box="[870,1056,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has yellow and white inner tepal morphs and a wider geographic range in 
<collectingRegion box="[593,786,1526,1553]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan, Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[844,944,1526,1552]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
